# Project Overview: Tapo H100 Device Lister

This Python application connects to a TP-Link Tapo H100 Hub and lists all connected child devices with their status and details.

## Main Components

- **[src/tapo_chatter/main.py](mdc:src/tapo_chatter/main.py)**: Core implementation that connects to the hub and displays device information
- **[src/tapo_chatter/config.py](mdc:src/tapo_chatter/config.py)**: Configuration handling via environment variables
- **[pyproject.toml](mdc:pyproject.toml)**: Project configuration and dependencies

## Features

- Discovers and lists all child devices connected to a Tapo H100 hub
- Displays device information across two detailed tables
- Checks network connectivity to the hub
- Securely handles authentication
- Color-codes signal strength indicators
- Displays critical status information for various sensor types

## Setup Requirements

- Python 3.13
- Environment variables in `.env` file:
  - `TAPO_USERNAME`: Your Tapo account email
  - `TAPO_PASSWORD`: Your Tapo account password
  - `TAPO_IP_ADDRESS`: IP address of your H100 hub

## Running the Application

```bash
python -m tapo_chatter.main
```
